This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with scene parsing, which is a task related to image understanding. The use of a multiscale convolutional network for feature extraction also supports this assumption. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of a classifier for object recognition and segmentation suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques for selecting the optimal covers suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
